omising, but I have concerns about dependency on library paths.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting potential issues**\\n\\nI'm considering if there's an issue with Ddeml being initialized unsuccessfully by other tests in the same suite, since the test order isn't specified. I think that existing tests, like DdemlUtilInnerMessageLoopWrapperTest, are calling new DdeClient(). I should check whether DdemlUtil has any fields related to DdeClient that might be affecting the tests. It looks like inspecting the top source could help clarify any misconfiguration or initialization problems.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Pm9lpZYH0cl4jF0GgBHVVGdf|fc_0af6d12d73532e180169f2dc8643c481a3a0500e4a403ce6c3", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/main/extracted/com/sun/jna/platform/win32/DdemlUtil.java", "offset": 1, "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3637, "output": 918, "cacheRead": 13312, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17867, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777523832411, "responseId": "resp_0af6d12d73532e180169f2dc78cc0481a3869ec6c590621f27"}}
